sentences: Sumire Morohoshi (諸星 すみれ, Morohoshi Sumire, born April 23, 1999) is a Japanese actress, voice actress and singer from Kanagawa Prefecture.
Born in Kanagawa Prefecture in 1999, she was born with the right side of her body paralysed.
The paralysis was cured in the first few months of her life.
In 2006, at the age of seven, she voiced Carrie in the anime series Red Garden and was shocked by the performance of Takehito Koyasu that she co-starred.
In 2009, at the age of nine, Morohoshi voiced Nina Tucker in Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood and the staff and co-stars evaluated that her "acting is skillful."
Since 2009, she has been active as a voice actor, but she also performs in television dramas and on stage as an actress.

In the fall of 2019, debuted as a singer from the record label FlyingDog with the track "Pure White", which was used for the opening theme to Ascendance of a Bookworm, and released as part of her debut album Smile.
